		<title>Productive Tools That Every Developer Should Know</title>
		<link>https://www.aryausa.com/blog/productive-tools-that-every-developer-should-know</link>
					<comments>https://www.aryausa.com/blog/productive-tools-that-every-developer-should-know#respond</comments>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Admin]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2020 08:14:45 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Productive Tools for Developers]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Projects]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Solutions]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Application and Software Development]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Best Software Development Company in USA]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Custom Development Software]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Custom Software Development Services in USA]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Productive tools]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[software development]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Software Development Company in USA]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.aryausa.com/blog/?p=1248</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Developers are the main players of any IT project, especially when it comes to creating important software, tools or making sure it all works properly.</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog/productive-tools-that-every-developer-should-know">Productive Tools That Every Developer Should Know</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog">Aryavrat</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The developer is the main player of any IT project, especially when it comes to creating important software, tools or making sure it all works properly. And that is a challenging and responsible job.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Taking part in the process of </span><a href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog/how-to-successfully-outsource-for-your-small-business" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Custom Software Development</a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">makes developer&#8217;s work difficult. They are always busy and they need to stay focused not to make any mistakes. Sometimes their most of the time is wasted in choosing the right tool.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Picking the right tool for the right job is probably the most crucial skill. It is necessary for the developer to constantly be on the lookout for new tools that increase productivity and happiness. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">There are so many different software tools on the market that aim to ease the process of getting things done. Here’s the pick of the best productivity tools for the developer.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Zoom</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Zoom is the best tool to handle all real-time communications. It is the</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> leading video conferencing software application. Zoom allows you to virtually interact with co-workers or employers when in-person meetings aren&#8217;t possible. </span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Zoom&#8217;s features are:</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><b>One-on-one meetings:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Host unlimited one-on-one meetings even with the free plan.</span></li>
<li><b>Group video conferences:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Host up to 500 participants.</span></li>
<li><b>Screen sharing:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Meet one-on-one or with large groups and share your screen with them so they can see what you see.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Insomnia</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Insomnia is a free and powerful REST API Client for cookie management, code generation, and environment variables with authentication for Mac, Windows, and Linux. It is the best tool to test your queries and requests and also supports GraphQL out of the box.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Insomnia&#8217;s Features are:</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">SSL client certificates</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">JSONPath and XPath</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Preview rendered HTML</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Query parameter editor</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cloud sync and sharing</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Responsive interface</span></li>
</ul>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Trello</span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Trello is the smartest collaboration application for agile teams. The most specific thing about Trello is its board &amp; card system: separate projects are marked with boards, within which there is a card for every task. Another specific function is the streamlined voting system where employees can support/disapprove a project and take action in less than no time. Trello is the best tool for small lightweight teams who move fast.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Trello&#8217;s Features are:</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Well-Organized Board &amp; Card System:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> With a board assigned for each project, and a card for each task, there all assignments are in order and can be tracked with specific performance lists.</span></li>
<li><b>Collaboration:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Teams can participate in important discussions in both group meetings and one-to-one chat sessions. It also allows you to upload files, notes, and diatribes.</span></li>
<li><b>Integrations:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Trello works with literally every third-party app/system, extension, or plugin.</span></li>
<li><b>Security:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Trello is designed to comply with the highest security standards, and uses a bank-level encryption mechanism.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Jira</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Known as one of the most popular developer’s productivity tools. Jira is used for project management which is a perfect choice for Agile teams who respect collaboration and pay a lot of attention to teamwork. Jira also allows developers to prioritize feature development, create personalized lists, fill the backlog and discuss tasks.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Jira Features are: </span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Customizable dashboards and wallboards</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Scrum, Kanban, and Scrumban boards</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bugs and defect management</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Customizable workflows</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Integration with flexible REST APIs</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Advanced security and administration</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seamless source and issue integration</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">To-do List</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">An app that keeps you organized and productive. In the To-do list developers can manage a list of things to do with simple commands. With a To-do List, you can manage all the tasks according to the time and prioritize tasks along with additional tasks, filter and group them, and archive them.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">To-do list Features are: </span></h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Stay in Sync:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Link the app to a Google or Toodledo.com account and your devices will be perfectly in sync. Sync can occur automatically.</span></li>
<li><b>Share and Collaborate:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Assign tasks to others and track status.</span></li>
<li><b>Status Tracking:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Tracks which tasks are being actively worked on, which are postponed, and which are waiting on someone.</span></li>
<li><b>Time Tracking:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> A built-in timer is included that Keeps track of both the estimated and actual length of tasks.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">CodeStream</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For easily sharing code-level knowledge. Codestream supports every programming language and enables you to discuss code with your team without ever using a pull request. Just highlight a code block and type a comment for intuitive, easy issue resolution.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Codestream Features are: </span></h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Version Control:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> It gives the ability to project teams to share the same source code repository and keep changes in sync between workstations.</span></li>
<li><b>Collaboration:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Helps you safely share data with only those matters and improves your teamwork.</span></li>
<li><b>Chat (Messaging):</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Through chatting users can collaborate better by exchanging views and collecting information.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Walrus.ai</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Automate your QA testing. Walrus.ai is a well-organized and lightweight solution to in-house automated testing or manual QA that can save money and effort on testing your code by providing full end-to-end testing via a single API call.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Walrus.ai Features are: </span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">UI and functional testing</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">API testing</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Third-party integration testing</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Test analytics</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Test scheduling</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">InVision</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">InVision is built for modern graphic designers with flexible workflow and support for Multiple Pages and Artboards.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Transform your Web &amp; Mobile designs into clickable, interactive Prototypes and Mockups. Share and Collaborate on them with others.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">InVision Features are: </span></h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Faster Creation:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> develop a web page or application with a faster creation experience with Invision&#8217;s Vector Drawing Tool.</span></li>
<li><b>Responsive Layout:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> The InVision Studio layout engine enables developers to adjust and scale their design to suit any standard of the screen &#8211; no matter how small or large it might be.</span></li>
<li><b>Speedy Prototyping: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">InVision Studio provides you a comprehensive gesture list to choose from, drag and drop prototyping, and an instant playback setting so you can show people what you&#8217;ve changed in your version.</span></li>
<li><b>Amazing Open API:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> InVision Studio works on an open API with an extensive application integration ecosystem.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Conclusion</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When it comes to programming, Picking the right tool is probably the most important thing for the developer. These are the Best Productivity Tools for the Developer to organize tasks, automate the process, facilitate relevant communications, time-managing processes and stay productive. An Award-Winning <a href="https://www.aryausa.com/custom-software-development">Custom Software Development Company in  the USA</a>,  For more info, let&#8217;s connect at </span><a href="sales@aryausa.com">sales@aryausa.com</a></p>
