		<item>
		<title>Device Rooted? What to do now</title>
		<link>https://www.aryausa.com/blog/device-rooted-what-to-do-now</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Admin]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 30 Nov 2015 09:18:42 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Solutions]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.aryausa.com/blog/?p=322</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Make sure that you have actually rooted your Android Smartphone. You can do that by a number of ways, there are plenty of root checker apps that available in the Play Store.</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog/device-rooted-what-to-do-now">Device Rooted? What to do now</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog">Aryavrat</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Check Root: </strong>Make sure that you have actually rooted your Android Smartphone. You can do that by a number of ways, there are plenty of root checker apps that available in the Play Store.</p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;"><strong>Flash Custom ROMs</strong> – One of the most entertaining advantage of rooting device is being able to install and flash Custom ROM .with rooted device you can make your phone more interactive as well as much more great tweaks with custom ROMs.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;"><strong>Play HD Games &#8211;</strong> There are many things you can do with your rooted device. You can play some heavy games on your android smart phone. Even if you smart phone did not support them before you rooted it.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;"><strong>Install CWM</strong> &#8211; CWM stands for Clock works mod Recovery. Now this recovery is a custom recovery and it would replace the stock recovery that is pre-installed on your Android Device. It allows you to flash “Zips” right from the phone itself, without using any PC tool.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;"> <strong>Increase internal memory</strong> – As there are many devices which have low internal memory and it create difficulties to install apps. With rooted phone you can increase your device’s internal memory.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;"><strong>Increase RAM of your device</strong> – With android phone you can do many things and one of them is you can increase your phone’s RAM. There are many ways and apps that can help you to maximize you smart phone’s RAM. You can increase your RAM by portioning the SD card.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;"><strong>Overclocking</strong> – The other advantage of rooting your device is Overclocking. Overclocking is a process by which you just increase the clocking speed of the processor in your Android Smartphone. With this you can increase your phone’s speed.</li>
</ul>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog/device-rooted-what-to-do-now">Device Rooted? What to do now</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog">Aryavrat</a>.</p>
