		<item>
		<title>9 Things You Are Doing Wrong on Your iPhone</title>
		<link>https://www.aryausa.com/blog/9-things-you-are-doing-wrong-on-your-iphone</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Admin]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 23 Nov 2015 10:11:28 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[APP BULLETIN]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Solutions]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.aryausa.com/blog/?p=278</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Many people consider their iPhone as precious possession and  there’s a good chance that you are not treating your phone as well as you should be.</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog/9-things-you-are-doing-wrong-on-your-iphone">9 Things You Are Doing Wrong on Your iPhone</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog">Aryavrat</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Many people consider their iPhone as precious possession and  there’s a good chance that you are not treating your phone as well as you should be.  Here are some things you might be doing wrong:</p>
<ul>
<li>iPhones are not really designed to withstand with hot and super cool weather. Using your iPhone outside when it’s less than 32 degrees or over 95 degrees can drain the battery or even shut it off temporarily. So wherever you are out in extreme weather, keep your phone turn off or atleast in pocket</li>
<li>Use a soft lint-free cloth in order to clean your iPhone.</li>
<li>Many people have their Wi-Fi and Bluetooth on forever which is wrong. keeping these on all the time will also drain the battery. If you want to save your iPhone battery then shut the Bluetooth and Wi-Fi off when you aren’t using it.</li>
<li>People thinks that Apple charges are expensive so they prefer off brand charger. As Apple chargersmay be expensive, but they are worth the investment. Using off brands chargers can cause damage to your iPhone and can drain ypur battery life.</li>
<li>Keep your iPhone brightness settings to average. It can save your battery life.</li>
<li>Many people do not lock their iPhones with passcode. If you are not using passcode, there is a possibility to stolen your personal information. Having a passcode on your iPhone is the easiest way to protect your privacy from thieves or everyone around.</li>
<li>Do not turn off your iPhone periodically, it degrade your iPhone battery life.</li>
<li>Charging your iPhone for too long time can make your battery damage and actually make battery die quickly.</li>
<li>When you installed any app, it ask you if you want to allow for push notification or not. Don’t allow for push notification unless you absolutely have to.</li>
<li>Apps like Uber and Maps need access to your &#8220;location services&#8221; to work properly, Turned off your location. App will tell you when they need you to turn on that feature</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog/9-things-you-are-doing-wrong-on-your-iphone">9 Things You Are Doing Wrong on Your iPhone</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog">Aryavrat</a>.</p>
