		<item>
		<title>8 Easy Tips For Taking Beautiful Pictures From iPhone</title>
		<link>https://www.aryausa.com/blog/8-easy-tips-for-taking-beautiful-pictures-from-iphone</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Admin]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sat, 21 Nov 2015 09:59:18 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Solutions]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.aryausa.com/blog/?p=268</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Nowadays everyone loves photography and if you use your iPhone in right way you can take awesome pictures. Apple included very excellent hardware and smart software to make it smart.</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog/8-easy-tips-for-taking-beautiful-pictures-from-iphone">8 Easy Tips For Taking Beautiful Pictures From iPhone</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog">Aryavrat</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Nowadays everyone loves photography and if you use your iPhone in right way you can take awesome pictures. Apple included very excellent hardware and smart software to make it smart. There are some ways to take great looking pictures.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Use two hands to handle your iPhone</strong> – To take better pictures hold on your device with two hands. As iPhone device is light and thin, but still it can move while taking pictures. if possible, Rest your phone on something sturdy surface.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Use</strong> <strong>HDR over Flash</strong> – Use HDR instead of the flash when you’re faced with tricky lighting conditions. If you take a picture from HDR setting, your iPhone will take 3 pictures very quickly and paste these images to make a better lit image.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Download third party apps</strong> – Downloading third party apps like camera+ and snapseed can make your pictures more effective. These apps are incredible camera photos apps. You can control the exposure and focus points independently.</li>
<li><strong>Don’t use digital zoom</strong> – Don’t use digital zoom while taking a picture. Because digital zooming makes your image grainy and pixelated and can makes it even harder to take a sturdy image. if you want to take something close up actually walk up to it, get close and click.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Shoot the same thing with a few times</strong> – You can just take multiple shots of the same thing and one of them will be vastly better than the others.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Hold on and tap to lock focus</strong> –iPhone allows you to lock focus while taking picture. Simply tap the screen where you want to set focus and exposure, but instead of releasing your finger, hold it down for a couple of seconds. A larger square will appear where your finger is along with a yellow AE/AF LOCK sign.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Look for good light</strong> &#8211; Keep the sun at your back or stay in the shade. The pictures will definitely look better.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Shoot with burst mode</strong> &#8211; Apple included burst mode originally for snapping clear pictures of moving subjects, but it also works well when your camera is moving too. By snapping images in quick succession, You can get a clear shot.</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog/8-easy-tips-for-taking-beautiful-pictures-from-iphone">8 Easy Tips For Taking Beautiful Pictures From iPhone</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog">Aryavrat</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
