		<item>
		<title>7  Ways to spare Storage Space In iPhone/ iPad</title>
		<link>https://www.aryausa.com/blog/7-ways-to-spare-storage-space-in-iphone-ipad</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Admin]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 19 Nov 2015 10:48:11 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Solutions]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.aryausa.com/blog/?p=254</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Might be you don't know that there are many junk files in your device that consumes a lot of space and that make your phone slow.</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog/7-ways-to-spare-storage-space-in-iphone-ipad">7  Ways to spare Storage Space In iPhone/ iPad</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog">Aryavrat</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Might be you don&#8217;t know that there are many junk files in your device that consumes a lot of space and that make your phone slow. With a little knowledge you can make a ton of storage space  available on your device</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Clear Safari History And Website Data</strong> &#8211; If you haven’t cleared Safari data in a while, clear it. Because in some cases clearing it can help you to free 1GB+ of storage space on your iPhone or iPad.</li>
</ol>
<ol start="2">
<li><strong>Stop using Photo Stream</strong> &#8211; If you have photo Stream turned on, off it.Because Your iPhone&#8217;s Photo Stream automatically synchronize  your last 1,000 photos across your devices.  That means it&#8217;s storing 1,000 photos &#8212; about 1 GB &#8212; twice.</li>
</ol>
<ol start="3">
<li><strong>Delete Large iMessage Threads</strong> &#8211; Sharing a lot of photos and videos via iMessage can take a ton of storage space on your device. Deleting such photo/video can claim back quite a lot of space on your device.</li>
</ol>
<ol start="4">
<li><strong>Sign up for a streaming music service</strong> &#8211; The days of storing all your songs on your device has gone. So delete all the music stored locally and stream via cloud. It can save a valuable space on your device.</li>
</ol>
<ol start="5">
<li><strong>Update To Latest iOS Version</strong> &#8211; If you are on an early version of iOS and don’t worry about your jailbreak, then update it to the latest versions of iOS to take away a lot of storage space from iOS devices. To update to latest version of iOS via OTA, head to Settings -&gt; General -&gt; Software Update and update form there.</li>
</ol>
<ol start="6">
<li><strong>Use Google+ or Dropbox for storing photos</strong> &#8211; You might not want to take all your photos off your phone, and you don&#8217;t have to. But you can save space by having your photo library back up automatically to a cloud storage system.</li>
</ol>
<ol start="7">
<li><strong>Delete apps, you dont need</strong> &#8211; There are many apps you download in your device and used it only once. If you don’t use those apps, Delete them. Because there are many apps in your  device that are  only 10MB to 50MB in size and games can be 500MB to 1GB in size but they may contain a cache files to help them load content faster and cache files can take large storage space on your device.So delete those apps that you are not using.</li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog/7-ways-to-spare-storage-space-in-iphone-ipad">7  Ways to spare Storage Space In iPhone/ iPad</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.aryausa.com/blog">Aryavrat</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
