										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>Apple’s annual developers conference</strong> also called as <strong>WWDC</strong> (world wide developers conference) is set to kick off on June 8<sup>th</sup> 2015 with a Keynote at 10.00 am PDT in San Francisco. It will give a wonderful platform for the eager developers to show off their coolest apps for the Apple Watch</p>
<h1>Here are some of the expected highlights to look out, at the love fest of Apple’s WWDC</h1>
<ul>
<li>Apple’s debut on its own streaming music service</li>
<li>Cool Apple Watch apps</li>
<li>Updates to Mac OSX and IOS (as usual Apple mostly focuses on software development and updates)</li>
<li>New Software Development Kits that gives the ability to make direct use of Apple Watch’s microphone, sensor and scrolling digital crown instead of relying on the Iphone’s function.</li>
</ul>
